        "created_at": "2024-02-20T20:05:50.862Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The issue with hardware acceleration bugs has been known about for years and the recommended solution has always been to launch via the command line using --disable-gpu.</p>\n<p>I’ve just installed a new RTX4060 in my rig and the issues are so bad as to render Signal Desktop unusable. I’m sick of having to launch using the command line. Is there any way to add this to a config file or something to permanently disable hardware acceleration?</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 7,
        "updated_at": "2024-02-21T11:11:54.071Z",
